    <note>Zeng(1) Xiaoxu [1694] Same generational name as Gongliang's [8136] sons. He denounced Cai(1) Jing [1649] and was purged and banished to Lingnan; later rehabilitated and made prefect of Tanzhou where he gained merit for defeating and pacifying the Yao aboriginals; and finally, as prefect of Qingzhou in Shandong, he trained a militia that the Jin feared to attack. Cai(1) Kang's [1653] son-in-law, father-in-law of Su(1) Song's [8116] son, Xi(b) [3758]. SHY:ZG, 43.6b-7b. CBD, 4, 2824-5.</note>
